      • initialize

        public void initialize​(int rows,
                       int cols,
                       char[][] rep)
                throws InvalidMapException
        This function instantiates and initializes cells, destTiles, crates to the correct map elements (the # char means a wall, @ the player, . is unoccupied Tile, lowercase letter is crate on a Tile, uppercase letter is an unoccupied DestTile).
        Parameters:
        rows - The number of rows in the map
        cols - The number of columns in the map
        rep - The 2d char array read from the map text file
        Throws:
        InvalidMapException - Throw the correct exception when necessary. There should only be 1 player.

      • movePlayer

        public boolean movePlayer​(Map.Direction d)
        Attempts to move the player in the specified direction. Note that the player only has the strength to push one crate. It cannot push 2 or more crates simultaneously. The player cannot walk through walls or walk beyond map coordinates.
        Parameters:
        d - The direction the player wants to move
        Returns:
        Whether the move was successful

      • moveCrate

        private boolean moveCrate​(Crate c,
                          Map.Direction d)
        Attempts to move the crate into the specified direction by 1 cell. Will only succeed if the destination implements the occupiable interface and is not currently occupied.
        Parameters:
        c - The crate to be moved
        d - The desired direction to move the crate in
        Returns:
        Whether or not the move was successful

      • isOccupiableAndNotOccupiedWithCrate

        public boolean isOccupiableAndNotOccupiedWithCrate​(int r,
                                                   int c)
        Parameters:
        r - The row coordinate
        c - The column coordinate
        Returns:
        Whether or not the specified location on the grid is a location which implements Occupiable, yet does not currently have a crate in it. Will return false if out of bounds.
